rComments: Very caring about students and regularly asks how the semester is going. His exams are fair and he is available outside of class to help students master the concepts.
Absolute legend, best Chem Eng prof at uO
Amazing

He knows fluid flow is tricky and really takes the time to make sure you know the content. If you don't get something in class, see him after or use his office hours because he will take the time to go through it in detail with you. Such a gem and one of the nicest profs I have had at this school.
Amazing lectures, love this man.
By far, my best prof in the whole university. Unbelievable how nice and caring and most importantly a great teacher ! He really made me think I could do chem eng once again !

Fluid flow is kind of tricky but Dr. Macchi is a great professor and he makes the course as simple as he possibly can. The exam material was very similar to the examples he's given us and the midterm was true to the course material.

Macchi is a really great prof, he wants to help students and does a great job of simplifying concepts. Fluid flow is a challenging but very manageable course. Study lots for the midterm because the class is only graded on a couple of things. Lectures are really important if you are looking to understand concepts and not just memorize examples.
Great Prof, really easy to talk to and cares about students.

Dr. Macchi is the best prof I've had so far. He's genuine and has a good sense of humour. To do well in his class, make sure you do the DGD and assignment questions and make sure you do the independent reading for the final! He tends to figure some things out on the fly (like exact due dates and other logistics), so stay up to date on what he says!
Probably the best prof I have ever had. The class is really hard but he is amazing so it balances out. The midterm is very hard, the exam is also hard but fair.

For a chemical engineering course he was very fair in terms of marking and his lectures were well taught. His tests are fair, if you do the assignments and DGD your good to go, no surprises. The presentation and design project are grade boosters.

Best professor in the chemical engineering department. He is very caring and teaches very well. His midterm was difficult but his exam was extremely fair (and open laptop). What he says is covered for the midterm was actually the opposite of what was there (so beware of his little trick). His lectures are worth attending.
Most caring professor in uOttawa. I was touched by the level of empathy, and compassion he showed for his students. Exemplary professor, and human being. Take care Professor Macchi.
Great professor. Makes chemical Engineering very understandable and will even help out in other classes if the professors are not very good. I definitely recommend this professor and this course.

Midterm was very simple, but final was tough. Nevertheless, he is an amazing professor that cares about his students. Very fair professor. You will not understand a word in the lecture, but reading the material at home will clear things up. Group project is long and will take alot of your time. Hard course, study well for it.

Very kind professor!  I found the lectures to be somewhat confusing and the material to be quite difficult. However, he is very clear in his expectations for the midterm and final, making the course easy to study for. Design project was brutal.

Great professor. Cares about his students and has a great sense of humour. He's extremely helpful during his office hours and doesn't hesitate to lend a hand. Pay attention and keep up with the course material

I thoroughly enjoyed having Dr. Macchi as my prof for Fluid Mechanics. He's proven to be very knowledgeable and easily approachable. The tests were fair, and his expectations towards the students were clear. On top of that, he has a good sense of humour. Very good prof!

Probably the best prof I've had so far. He somehow manages to keep your attention even during 8:30am classes. Understand the examples from class and the assignments and you'll do good. Simply an awesome, fair and friendly prof.

He is a nice teacher, with great qualities. All the students look up to him. The best way to describe him: ?He?s a teacher with a big heart?. If you do your homework and listen in the course, exam won?t be a problem.
Very nice prof. Communicates well with students and he's one of the best prof that I've had so far. Exams are easy if you do your assignments and understand them.

He is a nice and fair prof, no better way to describe him. One of the most popular profs in the department. His exams are fair,so just master the assignments and the examples and you won't have any problems.If you find him hard, I fear for you when you'll get Taylor.

Also teaches 2717. Both classes are easy thanks to his amazing teaching skills. Always there to help. Perfectly bilingual making it easy for everyone to understand. Probably the best prof CHG has to offer. Teaches both English and French section.
Best prof I've ever had. Very clear, cares for how his students do and the exams are no surprise.
Very good prof. He teaches very well and is a great guy. Always there to help you. He was made for teaching
An extremely helpful prof. with a very nice personality. A hardworking and enthusiastic person. I believe in his abilities and predict he will have a very bright future.
Very very cute, always there to help you.
Very cute young professor. Extremely friendly and funny. Available for questions or just to talk.
